<h2>General Info</h2>

<h3>To become a customer and place your first order:</h3>
<p>To become a customer, go to our <a href="market/signup.php">sign-up page</a> and fill out the required information. After you are signed up in our system, you will receive an email notifying you that you may place your first order. To order, come back to the <a href="home_delivery.php">Home Delivery</a> area, click on <a href="place_an_order.php">Place an Order</a>, enter your password (which you created when you signed up) and you will enter our online market. To view our market before you sign up, take a <a href="market.php" target="_blank">market tour</a>.</p>

<h3>Your bin</h3>
<p>Localmotive Organic Delivery is easy. Every week we offer a selection of produce, fruit, bulk goods, bakery, meats, dairy, beverages, and cleaning supplies, all displayed on our online market. Ordering is as simple as the click of your mouse on desired items, which are added to your online shopping list. The minimum order is $25 for custom and surprise orders, with free delivery to your home or office. We deliver to Summerland, Naramata, Penticton, OK Falls, Oliver, Osoyoos and all points in between.</p>

<h3>Online ordering</h3>
<h4>Ordering</h4>

<p>Custom orders can be placed by Sunday evening for Tuesday and Wednesday deliveries. Orders placed by Wednesday evening will be delivered on Fridays.</p>

<p>Orders are packed according to when they are received, so the sooner you can order, the more likely we can provide all of the items that you order. A new list of items is posted every Friday afternoon, and a reminder e-mail titled "Market is Ready" is sent out to help you remember to place your order.</p>

<p>Once signed in, you are taken to the Online Market. The market is divided into several different sections, each with a list of products. Click on the picture of the section that you would like to see. Browse the list of products by scrolling down the list, and choose products by typing in your desired quantity and pressing the '+' button. Items selected are transferred over to your shopping list, and a total for your order is tallied up as you choose more items. Once you have successfully submitted your order, a receipt of the transaction is sent to your email address. Occasionally an order does not go through properly, and a good indication of this is when you do not receive a receipt to your email account. In this case, please contact us for further assistance.</p>

<p>Surprise Orders are recurring orders that you set up to suit your regular dietary needs. Surprise orders can be mixed produce bin orders, starting at $25, containing a variety of fruits and vegetables at the best prices we can find. Or choose an assortment of baking or dairy that you like to have around consistently. These orders can be changed as you figure out your ideal surprise bin, by visiting the market and altering your surprise bin contents.</p>
   
<h4>Products</h4>
<p>Because we would like to eventually only supply products from the Okanagan and BC, products are labeled according to where they come from; town names or abbreviations of provinces/states are used to do this. Also, we go to extreme lengths to have your items harvested or baked only one or two days before it arrives at your doorstep! That is the definition of fresh!</p>
<p>All items are certified organic, unless otherwise indicated.</p>  
<p>If you have ideas for products you would like to see us carry, please send us a note at the bottom of your order in the comments section.</p>

