<h4>Cancelling or missing an order</h4>
<p>If you would like to cancel your order for the week, you must notify us three days in advance of your scheduled delivery.  You may cancel two deliveries in a row, but we reserve the right to replace you with a member on our waiting list if you do not continue with your schedule of deliveries.</p>

<h4>Credit</h4>
<p>Credit is given towards your next purchase for any items that are not to your satisfaction, or that are out of stock. Notify us if you are unsatisfied and we will add credit to your next purchase using our online accounting system. We add any credit to your account three days following your delivery, and this amount will be automatically deducted from the total of your next order.</p>

<h4>Payment</h4>
<p>Total price for your order is indicated once you have clicked on the &quot;Submit Order&quot; button. Payment is made upon delivery of your bin. Localmotive accepts cash, cheques made out to Localmotive, or credit card. Pre-payment for multiple bins is easy with our online accounting system.</p> 
<p>To pay by credit card, you may choose to do so once you have completed ordering. You are taken to a secure PayPal site, where you can set up an account, and payment is made directly through this account to Localmotive. You will be taken to PayPal to complete payments each time you order online. A 3% fee is added for credit card payments.</p>
<!--<p>A $12 refundable deposit is required for your bin and cold packs, and this will be only added to the price of your first delivery. The day of your next delivery, set out your bin from the previous delivery, and we'll take it home to be cleaned and reused. We keep track of bins that are not placed out, and will charge an extra $12 to your account after 2 bins are not returned.</p>-->

<h4>Composting</h4>
<p>As we will be picking-up your box from the previous week, you may leave compost scraps in the bin for us to take away, helping to reduce the volume of garbage waste. We will accept compost that is no older than 6 days old, is not cooked, and contains no meat products. We provide a compost bucket with a lid for each new customer, and you can set out this bucket with your old bin on your delivery day. We will empty the bucket and leave it there for you.</p>
<p>If we have not yet provided a bucket for you, please put your compost into a plastic bag without any holes or leaks in the bottom.</p>

<h4>Recipes</h4>
